The paper proposes a new type of graph neural network and evaluates its performance on graph classification and regression benchmarks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions that the learned representations correspond to chemical features in molecule data, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper introduces a new memory layer for GNNs, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
